# PRODUCTION BINARY RULES

## Single Binary Model
Production and test are the SAME binary. Default: web server / main. `--test`: self-evaluation suite.
No separate production crate.

## Binary Composition
Embed everything at runtime: HTML inline, assets via rust-embed, DB at runtime.
No external template files or asset dirs at runtime. Test suite compiled in, activated by flag.

## Core Crate Independence
Core crates must NOT depend on: web framework (axum), tower, rust-embed, clap, colored, tempfile.
Core error type uses plain integer status codes — framework-specific conversion stays in api layer.

## Database
Use runtime queries (not compile-time macros that require DATABASE_URL at build).
Timestamps as RFC3339. WAL journal mode where applicable. Create data dir automatically.

## Crypto
AES-256-GCM with random nonce; HKDF for key derivation; Argon2id for passwords.
Reject undersized ciphertext. Different context strings per key purpose.

## Graceful Shutdown
Respond to ctrl_c — both HTTP and HTTPS paths must shut down gracefully.
Close DB pool when server stops (if applicable).

## Release Build
Optimize for size: LTO, strip, panic=abort. See Cargo.toml for current profile.

## Dependencies
Document compatible versions in Cargo.toml. Avoid breaking upgrades without verification.
Axum, sqlx, reqwest must share compatible tokio/rustls stack.
